.TH "TEMPORAL.INSTANT.COMPARE" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.Instant.compare \- Temporal.Instant.compare()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Temporal.Instant.compare()\f[B]\f[R] static method
returns a number (\-1, 0, or 1) indicating whether the first instant
comes before, is the same as, or comes after the second instant.
It is equivalent to comparing the \f[CR]epochNanoseconds\f[R] of the two
instants.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
Temporal.Instant.compare(instant1, instant2)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]instant1\f[R]
A string or a \f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] instance representing the
first instant to compare.
It is converted to a \f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] object using the same
algorithm as \f[CR]Temporal.Instant.from()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]instant2\f[R]
The second instant to compare, converted to a
\f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] object using the same algorithm as
\f[CR]instant1\f[R].
.SS Return value
Returns \f[CR]\-1\f[R] if \f[CR]instant1\f[R] comes before
\f[CR]instant2\f[R], \f[CR]0\f[R] if they are the same, and \f[CR]1\f[R]
if \f[CR]instant1\f[R] comes after \f[CR]instant2\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using Temporal.Instant.compare()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] instant1 = Temporal.Instant.from(\(dq2021\-08\-01T12:34:56Z\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] instant2 = Temporal.Instant.from(\(dq2021\-08\-01T12:34:56Z\(dq);

console.log(Temporal.Instant.compare(instant1, instant2)); \f[I]// 0\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] instant3 = Temporal.Instant.from(\(dq2021\-08\-01T13:34:56Z\(dq);
console.log(Temporal.Instant.compare(instant1, instant3)); \f[I]// \-1\f[R]
.EE
.SS Sorting an array of instants
The purpose of this \f[CR]compare()\f[R] function is to act as a
comparator to be passed to \f[CR]Array.prototype.sort()\f[R] and related
functions.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] instants = [
  Temporal.Instant.from(\(dq2021\-08\-01T12:34:56Z\(dq),
  Temporal.Instant.from(\(dq2021\-08\-01T12:34:56+01:00\(dq),
  Temporal.Instant.from(\(dq2021\-08\-01T12:34:56\-01:00\(dq),
];

instants.sort(Temporal.Instant.compare);
console.log(instants.map((instant) \f[B]=>\f[R] instant.toString()));
\f[I]// [ \(aq2021\-08\-01T11:34:56Z\(aq, \(aq2021\-08\-01T12:34:56Z\(aq, \(aq2021\-08\-01T13:34:56Z\(aq ]\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
